                "display_name": "Saami Siddiqui"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1505415960,
            "creation_date": 1505413819,
            "body": "<p>I had a similar issue with one of my dependencies. I went to the <code>.m2/repository<\/code> directory and manually deleted the unwanted dependencies that were there. I only kept the version I wanted in the <code>m2<\/code> directory. Then I invalidated my caches and restarted IntelliJ IDEA. That seemed to have fixed the issue.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 46226053,
            "question_id": 34481300,
            "last_edit_date": 1505415960
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ba22aa9cb9fe8d2d714768d6f8e5c486?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 10367658,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 7646237,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7646237/d%c3%a1niel-apjok",
                "reputation": 1,
                "display_name": "D&#225;niel Apjok"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1687189507,
            "creation_date": 1687189507,
            "body": "<p>It's and old post but just in case, what worked for me in newer version (2023.1.2) is to delete manually the cached faulty version. It can be done by<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>In Project hierarchy find &quot;External Libraries&quot; and the faulty dependency in it.<\/li>\n<li>Right click -&gt; Open Library Settings (or Left click -&gt; F4)<\/li>\n<li>This will open &quot;Project Structure/Libraries&quot; (ctrl + shift + alt + s) with the dependency selected in the list.<\/li>\n<li>Click on the &quot;-&quot; icon on top of the list. Confirm. Reimport maven and it should download the correct version.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n",
            "answer_id": 76508192,
            "question_id": 34481300
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/364b2a1a765cbd232b64a2347fbc059e?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2794316,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2403836,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2403836/mr-nooby-noob",
                "reputation": 2332,
                "display_name": "mr nooby noob",
                "accept_rate": 72
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1696505769,
            "creation_date": 1696505769,
            "body": "<p>For me deleting the dependecy in my .m2 didnt help, neither did clearing the cache idea. In the end I just had to reclone my repo and it worked.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 77236754,
            "question_id": 34481300
